Package org.arl.goeuro.src

Sources of classes and interfaces of the GoEuroTest console application

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IArguments
    This interface is used to abstract the concept of arguments, in details here we specify all the functions used to save and check the arguments inserted by the user.
    IGoEuroApi
    This interface is used to abstract the GoEuro API concept, in details here we specify all the functions used to manage the API.
    IJSONConvert
    This interface is used to abstract the concept of JSON converter.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GoEuroTest
    This class contains the main method, this method, using an instance of MyArguments and one of MyClient, creates the console application for GoEuro Test.
    MyArguments
    This class implements the IArgument Interface to manage the arguments inserted by the user
    MyClient
    This class implements the IGoEuroApi and IJSONConvert interfaces.
